[2]
Date: Sat, 12 Feb 2005
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: VNA agency, 10 Feb 2005 [edited]
<http://www.vnagency.com.vn/newsA.asp?LANGUAGE_ID=2&CATEGORY_ID=29&NEWS_ID=138547>

Bird flu control efforts maintained during Tet
----------------------------------------------
The work to control bird flu has continued at grassroots levels
during the traditional new year festival, Tet.
According to the Agriculture and Rural Development Ministry's
Veterinary Department, only 2 new outbreaks of bird flu were reported
from 2 communes in the southern provinces of Dong Thap and Ben Tre on
9 Feb and in the morning of 10 Feb 2005. A total of 1050 ducks and
geese were culled.
However, no new outbreaks of bird flu have been reported in northern
Ha Nam province or southern Binh Phuoc province since 9 Jan 2005, and
in Ninh Thuan and Lam Dong provinces since 20 Jan 2005.
